X-WR-CALNAME:Weaver line disruption
BEGIN:VEVENT
DESCRIPTION:<a href="https://tfl.gov.uk/tube-dlr-overground/status/?Input=&lineIds=&dateTypeSelect=Future%20date&direction=&startDate=2026-06-10T21:45:00&endDate=2026-06-11T00:29:00">Disruption map.</a>\n\nWEAVER LINE: Monday 8\, Tuesday 9\, Wednesday 10 and Thursday 11 June\, after 2245 each evening\, no service between Hackney Downs and Cheshunt / Enfield Town. Use London Underground connections between Central London and Seven Sisters\, and for Rectory Road and Stoke Newington\, use Clapton station. Last trains operate at 2243 from Liverpool Street to Cheshunt (except on Wednesday when it is at 2213)\, 2250 from Enfield Town to Liverpool Street\, 2258 from Liverpool Street to Enfield Town and 2259 from Cheshunt to Liverpool Street. Replacement buses operate. PLEASE NOTE: Due to roadworks\, service L2 will not serve Theobalds Grove or Cheshunt and is revised to terminate at Waltham Cross (Lidl). This is around a 20 minute walk from Theobalds Grove and 40 minute walk from Cheshunt. For Cheshunt\, please use GREATER ANGLIA services where possible as there are no local bus services available between Waltham Cross\, Theobalds Grove and Cheshunt at the time of this closure.
DTEND:20260611T002900Z
DTSTART:20260610T214500Z
SUMMARY:Weaver line: Part Closure
UID:e764d02f-edbf-42e1-9983-8a533782aff4@e764.org
END:VEVENT
